modules.description: Provides session management operations including generating, retrieving, updating, and removing session data. Works with string-based keys, string values, and integer-based expiration periods. Used to handle session lifecycles in web applications, ensuring timely expiration and secure storage of user-specific data.

Handles cookie-based session management and persistent storage for HTTP servers, using CoHTTP, Webmachine, Async, and Lwt. Operates on session identifiers, cookie headers, and backend storage systems implemented via functors. Enables authenticated routes by validating session tokens stored in cookies against a configured backend.

Manages session data through operations that generate, retrieve, update, and delete entries using string keys, string values, and integer expiration times. Supports session lifecycle control, ensuring data is automatically removed after a specified duration. Enables secure, timed storage of user-specific information in web applications. Examples include storing user authentication tokens with a 30-minute expiration or updating a user's login status dynamically.
